{
  "texts": [
    "Building a comprehensive knowledge model capturing all the possible ways of performing an activity is challenging even for experts, and we are not aware of public ontologies comprehensively covering all the possible human activities and context situations.ADL-LLM has the same goal of knowledge-based approaches: using common-sense knowledge about human activities to recognize them.",
    "However, instead of relying on manually designed logic models, ADL-LLM leverages the knowledge implicitly encoded in pre-trained LLM to guarantee better generalization capabilities.",
    "Neuro-Symbolic Methods.Neuro-Symbolic AI (NeSy) methods combine the best from datadriven and knowledge-based worlds.",
    "Indeed, the goal of NeSy models is to combine symbolic reasoning and machine learning to mitigate data scarcity and improve the model's interpretability [27].",
    "Considering the HAR domain, logic formalisms have been used to refine the output of the data-driven model [8] or to infuse knowledge inside deep learning models [6,49]."
  ]
}